  "prompt": "How can someone subscribe to Facebook topics on Quora?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, there isn't a direct feature on Quora that allows you to subscribe to Facebook-related topics in the same way you might on social media platforms. However, you can still stay updated on Facebook-related discussions on Quora by following these steps:\n\n1. **Search for Facebook Topics**: Use the search bar on Quora to look for topics like \"Facebook,\" \"Facebook Marketing,\" or any specific subtopics you're interested in.\n\n2. **Follow Topics**: Once you find a relevant topic, click on it and select the \"Follow\" button. This will add the topic to your feed, and you\u2019ll see questions and answers related to Facebook in your Quora updates.\n\n3. **Follow People or Spaces**: You can follow individual users or Spaces on Quora that are known for sharing Facebook-related content or insights. Spaces are community-driven collections of questions and answers on specific themes.\n\n4. **Enable Notifications**: After following a topic or Space, adjust your notification settings to get alerts when new content is posted. This can be done by clicking the bell icon on the topic or Space page.\n\n5. **Engage with Content**: Upvote, comment on, or share posts about Facebook to signal your interest. Quora\u2019s algorithm may then prioritize similar content in your feed.\n\nIf you\u2019re looking for more specific or real-time updates about Facebook, consider using Facebook\u2019s own resources, such as its official blog, help center, or community forums. Additionally, following relevant hashtags or accounts on platforms like Twitter or Reddit might also help you stay informed.",
